{
  "Love Blind": {
    "type": [
      "Interpersonal",
      "Social"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>The flowers had been appearing outside Helian's office every morning for two weeks. Kalina had counted. Today there were seven, arranged in a neat row along the doorframe.</em></p>
      <p>"Someone has a secret admirer"</p>
      <p><em>Helian stepped over them without looking down.</em></p>
      <p>"Logistics left them. Something about base beautification."</p>
      <p><em>Kalina looked at the flowers. She looked at Helian. She opened her mouth.</em></p>
      <p>"Right, Beautification..."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You are completely and utterly blind to the intricacies of romance and romantic cues. This can lead to misunderstandings and missed opportunities in social interactions involving romantic interests.</li>
        <li>When performing a check that involves understanding or responding to romantic signals, you must reroll two dice showing (su) or (ex).</li>
        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Threatening Demeanor": {
    type: [
      "Interpersonal",
      "Social"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>The refugees had gathered near the south gate, waiting for someone to tell them where to go. Command sent Vasquez to direct them to the temporary shelters.</em></p>
      <p><em>She made it three steps into the crowd before a woman pulled her children behind her. A man near the front raised both hands, palms out, and backed away. The whole group shifted like a school of fish spotting a shadow overhead.</em></p>
      <p>"I'm here to help." <em>She kept her voice level.</em> "Shelters are this way."</p>
      <p><em>Nobody moved. A child started crying.</em></p>
      <p>"I could have sent someone else," <em>the Commander offered over the radio, too late.</em></p>
      <p>"Yeah. You could have."</p>
    """,
    description: """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Something about your appearance, posture, or demeanor makes people instinctively wary of you. Even when your intentions are entirely benign, strangers tend to assume the worst, and first impressions rarely land in your favor.</li>
        <li>When performing a check where appearing non-threatening would help (such as approaching a stranger peacefully or trying to calm a tense situation), you must reroll two dice showing (su) or (ex).</li>
        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Rival [Name]": {
    type: [
      "Interpersonal",
      "Social"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>The requisition form came back denied for the third time. Same clerk, same stamp, same vague citation of "inventory discrepancies." Leva stared at the paperwork.</em></p>
      <p>"He's doing this on purpose."</p>
      <p>"You don't know that."</p>
      <p>"I beat him for the liaison posting eight months ago. He's been losing my paperwork ever since." <em>She set the form down carefully, as if it might bite.</em> "Last week he told the quartermaster I'd already drawn my ammunition allotment. I hadn't."</p>
      <p>"So go over his head."</p>
      <p>"His supervisor plays cards with him every Thursday." <em>Leva smiled, thinly.</em> "He's patient. I'll give him that."</p>
    """,
    description: """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Someone has a personal vendetta against you, and they will go out of their way to make your life difficult. They may not be openly hostile, but they will use their influence and resources to undermine you whenever the opportunity arises.</li>
        <li>When performing a check where your rival's interference could complicate matters (such as requisitioning supplies through their department or persuading a mutual acquaintance), you must reroll two dice showing (su) or (ex).</li>
        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Missing Arm": {
    type: [
      "Physical"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>The crate was jammed against the wall at an angle, and Mack couldn't get the leverage he needed. He braced his shoulder against it and pushed, boots scraping on concrete, but without a second hand to grip the edge it kept slipping.</em></p>
      <p>"Need a hand?" <em>One of the new recruits jogged over, then froze, eyes dropping to the pinned sleeve.</em> "I, uh... sorry, I didn't mean..."</p>
      <p>"Just grab the other side."</p>
      <p><em>They moved the crate in silence. The recruit kept glancing at him like he wanted to say something. Mack saved him the trouble.</em></p>
      <p>"It's fine. Everyone says it."</p>
    """,
    description: """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You are missing one of your arms, either from birth, injury, or surgical removal. You have learned to compensate in most daily tasks, but certain physical activities remain significantly harder for you.</li>
        <li>When performing a check that would normally benefit from two hands (such as climbing a wall, steadying a heavy weapon, or carrying bulky equipment), you must reroll two dice showing (su) or (ex).</li>
        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Animal Aversion": {
    type: [
      "Interpersonal"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>The stray had been friendly with everyone in the squad. It ate from Volya's hand, slept at the foot of Harpsy's cot, and followed the Commander around the compound like a shadow.</em></p>
      <p><em>Then Nika rounded the corner, and the dog's ears went flat.</em></p>
      <p>"Easy, boy. I'm not going to..."</p>
      <p><em>The growl started low and built until the dog was backing away, hackles raised, teeth bared. Nika hadn't moved.</em></p>
      <p>"It's not personal," <em>the Commander offered.</em></p>
      <p>"It's always personal." <em>Nika watched the dog retreat behind a supply pallet.</em> "Every animal I've ever met has hated me. Cats, dogs, horses. A parrot tried to bite my ear off once."</p>
    """,
    description: """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Animals react to you with instinctive hostility or fear. Dogs growl, cats hiss, horses shy away. You have no idea why, and no amount of patience or gentle behavior seems to change it.</li>
        <li>When performing a check that involves interacting with an animal (such as calming a guard dog or riding a horse), you must reroll two dice showing (su) or (ex).</li>
        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  Insignificant: {
    type: [
      "Interpersonal",
      "Social"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>The briefing had been going for twenty minutes. Twice now, Petra had raised her hand. Twice, the officer's gaze had swept past her like she was part of the furniture.</em></p>
      <p>"Sir, the northern approach is..."</p>
      <p>"Hold that thought." <em>He turned to the sergeant.</em> "Kowalski, what's your read on the northern approach?"</p>
      <p><em>Kowalski said exactly what Petra had been trying to say. The officer nodded approvingly.</em></p>
      <p>"Good eye, Kowalski."</p>
      <p><em>Petra closed her mouth. Next to her, Harpsy winced in sympathy.</em></p>
    """,
    description: """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>People tend to look right through you. In conversations, your points get attributed to whoever speaks next. In crowds, you are the first person forgotten. It is not that people dislike you; they simply never register that you were there.</li>
        <li>When performing a check where being taken seriously matters (such as giving orders, making a persuasive argument, or trying to hold someone's attention), you must reroll two dice showing (su) or (ex).</li>
        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Lingering Fatigue": {
    type: [
      "Physical"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>Mechty had slept for eleven hours. Klukai had counted, because Klukai counted everything. Eleven hours, and when Mechty finally sat up, she looked exactly the same as when she had laid down.</em></p>
      <p>"I was going to wake you earlier. Commander intervened. You've slept for 11 whole hours."</p>
      <p>"Mm." <em>Mechty rubbed her eyes with the heel of her palm.</em> "Didn't help."</p>
      <p>"Eleven hours didn't help."</p>
      <p>"It never helps." <em>She reached for the manga on her nightstand, fumbled it, and let it fall open on her lap instead of picking it up again.</em> "I wake up and it's like I never slept. Every morning."</p>
      <p><em>Klukai watched her for a moment. Mechty's eyes were already half-closed again.</em></p>
    """,
    description: """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Your body holds onto exhaustion longer than it should. After exertion that would leave others winded for minutes, you are drained for hours. Recovery is slow, and pushing through only makes it worse.</li>
        <li>When performing a check where physical recovery matters (such as bouncing back after a forced march, staying alert after a long shift, or shaking off the effects of a recent injury), you must reroll two dice showing (su) or (ex).</li>
        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
