        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  Dependent: {
    type: [
      "Interpersonal",
      "Social"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>The mission briefing was clear: seventy-two hours in the field, no exceptions. Groza was already packed when Helena sat down in front of the door.</em></p>
      <p>"Helena. Please move."</p>
      <p>"No."</p>
      <p><em>Groza stared at her. Helena stared back.</em></p>
      <p>"The Commander will check on you. Krolik will be here."</p>
      <p>"Krolik doesn't read to me right. She does the voices wrong."</p>
      <p><em>Groza opened her mouth, closed it, and stood there for a long time. She picked up her radio.</em></p>
      <p>"Convoy, Groza. I need fifteen minutes."</p>
      <p>"We leave in ten."</p>
      <p>"Then I need ten minutes."</p>
      <p><em>She set her pack down, sat on the floor next to Helena, and opened the book to where they'd left off. She didn't do the voices right either, but Helena leaned against her arm anyway.</em></p>
    """,
    description: """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Someone in your life relies on you in a way you cannot ignore. Their needs create obligations that pull you away from your duties, and the guilt of neglecting either side is a weight that never fully lifts.</li>
        <li>When performing a check where your dependent's needs conflict with the task at hand (such as choosing between a mission and a personal emergency, or staying focused when you know they need you), you must reroll two dice showing (su) or (ex).</li>
        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
