    flavor: """
      <p><em>The checkpoint officer scanned the ID twice, then looked up.</em></p>
      <p>"Step aside, please."</p>
      <p>"There a problem?"</p>
      <p>"Your file's flagged. I need to make a call."</p>
      <p><em>The rest of the squad walked through without stopping. Colphne stood in the holding area for forty-five minutes while two officers confirmed what the system already knew: discharged, reinstated, conditionally cleared. All of it legal, all of it on paper, and none of it fast enough to keep her from feeling like a suspect every time she crossed a district line.</em></p>
      <p>"You're clear."</p>
      <p>"I know."</p>
