  "Foot in Mouth": {
    type: [
      "Social"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>The liaison dinner was going well until Krolik decided to make conversation.</em></p>
      <p>"So, how long have you been stationed here? You look like you've been here a while." <em>She paused.</em> "Not that you look old! You just look... experienced. Weathered? In a good way. Like leather."</p>
      <p><em>The diplomat's smile had frozen somewhere around "weathered."</em></p>
      <p>"Like good leather. Expensive leather."</p>
      <p>"Krolik." <em>The Commander's voice was very quiet.</em></p>
      <p>"I'm going to stop talking now."</p>
      <p>"Please."</p>
    """,
    description: """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You have an unerring instinct for saying exactly the wrong thing. It is never malicious; you simply open your mouth and the worst possible version of your thought falls out, often followed by increasingly desperate attempts to fix it that make everything worse.</li>
        <li>When performing a check where saying the right thing matters (such as making a diplomatic impression, de-escalating a tense situation, or delivering sensitive news), you must reroll two dice showing (su) or (ex).</li>
        <li>If the reroll causes you to fail the check, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "All Thumbs": {
    type: [
