  },
  "Risk-Averse": {
    type: [
      "Physical"
    ],
    flavor: """
      <p><em>The catwalk was the only way across. Thirty meters, no railing, rusted through in places. The squad went one at a time. Lotta was last.</em></p>
      <p><em>She put one foot on the grating. It groaned. She pulled her foot back.</em></p>
      <p>"Lotta, everyone else made it across. It holds."</p>
      <p>"Everyone else weighs less than me with full kit."</p>
      <p>"You weigh the same as Ullrid, and she jogged it."</p>
      <p><em>Lotta looked at the catwalk. She looked at the gap beneath it, four stories of open air and concrete. She had the numbers; the structure was sound. She knew it was sound. Knowing did not help.</em></p>
      <p>"I need a minute."</p>
      <p>"We don't have a minute."</p>
      <p><em>She crossed. Slowly, hands white on the guide cable, every step a negotiation between what she knew and what her legs were willing to do. On the other side, she sat down and did not stand up for a while.</em></p>
